description: 10/8/20, street repair/blacktop crew came out to lay down blacktop.  I was advised Misty Harbor Avenue was to be surfaced.  The street in front of my property was only surfaced to the mailbox.  My property extends to 18 inches past the privacy fence.  The crew told me that my property is in the middle of 44th Street Terrace and Misty Harbor so they were going to stop it at the mailbox.  NO, my entire property is, and always HAS been on Misty Harbor Ave.  I am NOT on 44th Street Terrace.  The crew told me that my address was 'pinging' on 44th Street Terrace and they were not going to surface the road past my mailbox.  This is absolutely ridiculous.  In front of my driveway, half is surfaced, the other half, unsurfaced.  I was told that all of Misty Harbor Avenue would be surfaced, which includes the entire frontage of my home.  Furthermore, my property and the street itself is 17 years' old, and has never been resurfaced.  It has been patched so many times it looks like a relief map of South America.  HOWEVER, the newer streets to the North, that are less than five years of age and are largely unoccupied/new construction, were resurfaced!!  I would think after paying 17 years' worth of SPECIALS that I could get an additional 25-30 feet of resurfacing done.  It absolutely looks ridiculous.  There are two houses to the East of my property that are on 44th Street Terrace that would also have to be resurfaced, as those properties and streets are the same age and were entirely skipped, as well.  The homes in this area are in the 260k range and this takes away from the neighborhood; plus the uneven pavement is a definite safety issue.  I am very concerned that the city believes my property is half on Misty Harbor Ave., and half on 44th Street Terrace - because I guess if the city decides to resurface 44th Street Terrace, they won't surface Misty Harbor Avenue??  That's ridiculous, as well.  Please respond and please come back and finish this job, because it is ugly, and needs review.  Lastly, I did call the Engineering department yesterday and left a message for a Mr. Foust or Faust - of course, no call back.  Since there seems to be quite a bit of confusion of where I really live, I would suggest someone get into their city car and come out here and actually look at the ridiculousness of the situation, and view the street.
address: 4437 Sw Misty Harbor Ave Topeka, KS, 66610, USA

description:
Silver Ford Escape parked on the street vehicle hasn't moved for several months.  A request was submitted recently and then closed.  I wasn't able to comment on the closed request so I am opening a new one in order to communicate my concerns.

I am at a loss to your response.  As a citizen I expect the laws of our city to be enforced when they are pointed out to our police department.  This car may not seem like it is bothering anything to the officer who only stops by for a brief minute but is does affect the quality of life for the neighbors in the area.  The car has not moved for over 6 months and there are even weeds starting to grow around the car.  Our city code clearly state a car cannot sit in one place for more than 48 hours.  This car has sat in the same location for an access of 4300 hours.  I am sure this vehicle fits the intent of the code.  I am not asking for a ticket I am asking that the police department take action and see that this car is moved and in compliance with our city code.  I have attached the code in case you are not aware of what you are expected to enforce.   In addition if that car is not registered to anyone at that house or someone nearby then I would think it would be considered abandoned having more of a reason to remove it.
10.60.100 Parking more than 48 hours.
It shall be unlawful for any person to park or permit the parking, storing or standing of any vehicle upon any public street or street parking in the city for any continuous period of more than 48 hours. Any motor vehicle which shall have been found to have remained parked, stored or located upon any of the public streets or parkings of the city for a continuous period of more than 48 hours shall be deemed a public nuisance and such nuisance may be abated in the manner provided in this article.

description: We bought this house in May 2019, and it began flooding shortly after we moved in. The owner said it had flooded once, and been repaired, but obviously lied.  It is the oldest house in the neighborhood; at least 3 of the surrounding houses, which were built up higher, have storm water drains flowing toward our back yard.  We moved back out and hired a firm to rip out the carpet and trim boards, and dry everything out last summer. Then we built a French drain and a berm, to divert the water around our property.  So far that had been working, but this morning the rain came too fast, and the river channel forced the storm water back through our downspout toward the house, so we had to re-route the gutter and bail for hours to keep the house from flooding again.  We will try to fix it, but there is only a 5 foot strip beside our house to work with, so we're pretty limited.  In addition, one of the workers we've hired thinks our water bill will be raised because we are diverting so much storm water into the front sewer, even though the water is not coming from our lot.  Could someone please come to look at this in person?

description: Noticed your water tower at 29th & California is now getting long overdue repairs.  With the few upgrades I have seen from the ground there has been one thing that has bothered me for some time which the city keeps ignoring.  Your lighting issues.  Even though it may not be required for the height it is common courtesy in many cities that all municipal water storage tanks be properly lit with FAA approved lighting regardless if the tower is in line of airspace travel in that area of town. This tower for some time has not had a very well lit light if working at all especially recently since they did minor repairs late last year when they added the new tank access on the top of the storage tank.  I would hope you are going to invest in a new improved light, a LED/strobe version similar to what the VA hospital went with on the top of their tower a few years ago. No maintenance, no bulbs to change.  It's money well spent.  I also noticed you had someone raise your lighting on your Montara area water tower a while back to clear over all the obstacles that have been added to that one. Great job. Only issue is you have the same issue on your water tower behind the Soldier Township Fire Department. That light fixture also needs raised and or upgraded. With LED fixtures taking place of the older incandescent bulbs you should probably budget to upgrade all the lighting on your towers over time. As far as the one behind Soldier Township Fire Department you can't see that light working well at night because it's being blocked by all the clutter that's been added.  If Forbes Field and the V.A. takes lighting that seriously so should the city.  I hope you will seriously look into these issues....

description: 10/8/20, street repair/blacktop crew came out to lay down blacktop.  I was advised Misty Harbor Avenue was to be surfaced.  The street in front of my property was only surfaced to the mailbox.  My property extends to 18 inches past the privacy fence.  The crew told me that my property is in the middle of 44th Street Terrace and Misty Harbor so they were going to stop it at the mailbox.  NO, my entire property is, and always HAS been on Misty Harbor Ave.  I am NOT on 44th Street Terrace.  The crew told me that my address was 'pinging' on 44th Street Terrace and they were not going to surface the road past my mailbox.  This is absolutely ridiculous.  In front of my driveway, half is surfaced, the other half, unsurfaced.  I was told that all of Misty Harbor Avenue would be surfaced, which includes the entire frontage of my home.  Furthermore, my property and the street itself is 17 years' old, and has never been resurfaced.  It has been patched so many times it looks like a relief map of South America.  HOWEVER, the newer streets to the North, that are less than five years of age and are largely unoccupied/new construction, were resurfaced!!  I would think after paying 17 years' worth of SPECIALS that I could get an additional 25-30 feet of resurfacing done.  It absolutely looks ridiculous.  There are two houses to the East of my property that are on 44th Street Terrace that would also have to be resurfaced, as those properties and streets are the same age and were entirely skipped, as well.  The homes in this area are in the 260k range and this takes away from the neighborhood; plus the uneven pavement is a definite safety issue.  I am very concerned that the city believes my property is half on Misty Harbor Ave., and half on 44th Street Terrace - because I guess if the city decides to resurface 44th Street Terrace, they won't surface Misty Harbor Avenue??  That's ridiculous, as well.  Please respond and please come back and finish this job, because it is ugly, and needs review.  Lastly, I did call the Engineering department yesterday and left a message for a Mr. Foust or Faust - of course, no call back.  Since there seems to be quite a bit of confusion of where I really live, I would suggest someone get into their city car and come out here and actually look at the ridiculousness of the situation, and view the street.

description: Noticed your water tower at 29th & California is now getting long overdue repairs.  With the few upgrades I have seen from the ground there has been one thing that has bothered me for some time which the city keeps ignoring.  Your lighting issues.  Even though it may not be required for the height it is common courtesy in many cities that all municipal water storage tanks be properly lit with FAA approved lighting regardless if the tower is in line of airspace travel in that area of town. This tower for some time has not had a very well lit light if working at all especially recently since they did minor repairs late last year when they added the new tank access on the top of the storage tank.  I would hope you are going to invest in a new improved light, a LED/strobe version similar to what the VA hospital went with on the top of their tower a few years ago. No maintenance, no bulbs to change.  It's money well spent.  I also noticed you had someone raise your lighting on your Montara area water tower a while back to clear over all the obstacles that have been added to that one. Great job. Only issue is you have the same issue on your water tower behind the Soldier Township Fire Department. That light fixture also needs raised and or upgraded. With LED fixtures taking place of the older incandescent bulbs you should probably budget to upgrade all the lighting on your towers over time. As far as the one behind Soldier Township Fire Department you can't see that light working well at night because it's being blocked by all the clutter that's been added.  If Forbes Field and the V.A. takes lighting that seriously so should the city.  I hope you will seriously look into these issues....

description:
On Dec. 26th, 2020, I contacted TPD because a neighbor who has a history of harassing me had come onto my property (past a no trespassing sign) and threatened me with a tree branch.  I was at the extreme west end of my driveway, working on insulating my chicken coop, when he walked up to me and began shouting about tree branches--which he routinely throws onto my property, preventing my vehicles from accessing the street or the west side of the driveway for parking.  That day the neighbor assaulted me verbally and physically, yet Officer D. Long, who responded, handcuffed me, placing my hands behind my back in a very uncomfortable position and fastened so tightly that I was left with bruising up and down my wrist and hand.  A video of this bruising is available through Dropbox.
Officer Long was made aware, as he was handcuffing me, that I have breast cancer and that he was being too rough, pulling at my car keys snagged over one finger and buising my other hand as a result.  The officer did not relent, but placed me in his cruiser and forced me to sit with hands cuffed behind me until the supervising officer, Officer Rose, showed up.  At that point, my hands were repositioned in front and the cuffs loosened before--at Officer Rose's insistance--I was cited and released.
The offending neighbor was simply cited for criminal trespass (though not assault, as far as I know)--he was not handcuffed and not forced to sit in a police car for half an hour on a holiday.  This persistant and inconsistent enforcement of the law has now created a record of my neighbor's harrassing behaviors toward me, the TPD practice of ignoring my evidence and statements about these incidents, and of Officer D. Long's refusal to correctly address me, using my title, Dr. Fritzler.
I believe Officer D. Long was unnecessarily rough in handcuffing me, showed hugely favored treatment to the accused--my neighbor, a Washburn law graduate, who regularly surveils my backyard with video cameras and spotlights, and antagonizes me on a near daily basis.  I further believe Officer Long's manner in taking reports, when he responds to my 911 calls, is disrespectful, rude and abusive.  When he is wrong, he refuses to acknowledge that fact and merely compounds the error with his continued selective application of the law.
The neighbor in previous weeks (on Dec. 1st) had followed me into the street, when I was looking for a missing cat, and shoved me three times--assaulting me.  Again, when I called TPD, Officer Ziegler responded and refused to cite the suspect/neighbor simply because the neighbor, when asked, denied having assaulted me or, presumably, having followed me into the street.
If the city needs a witness, though he would be hostile, another neighbor
came out into the street that evening when I positioned myself near his barking dogs in hopes the first neighbor (Mark (last name?) would leave me alone.  The second neighbor was extremely hostile about my being near his dogs and threatened to hit me while his mother yelled obscenities from their backdoor at 19th and SW Buchanan.  (!)
There seems to be grossly preferential and selective applications of laws regarding assault when TPD officers are called.  I was told by TPD officers on Dec. 27th, that what results an assault complaint brings are purely a matter of which officer responds.  This is not acceptable.  Further, when someone trespasses onto my property, I should be able to protect myself when they assault me--whether that is verbally, physically or both.
address: 1913 Sw Buchanan St Topeka, KS, 66604, USA

description:
This last summer the street department filled cracks and sealed (overlayed) all of the streets within Berkshire Greens neighborhood "except" the main street (SW Moundview dr) 'was not done'. The street has several 'cracks' that were not sealed and several are more than 2 inches wide and 15 feet in length.  Additionally, there are 'several areas' (one being at the intersection of Moundview dr. and Trivino ct [picture] ) that are literally breaking up in chunks. There are several of these areas within the 2 block stretch of Moundview dr, (starting on the east side entering the neighborhood.
It doesn't make much sense to have spent the money to seal all other streets and not Moundview dr. Sections of the street are deteriorating quickly and with the winter months it will surely accelerate.  Recommend the street be 'reevaluated' and necessary repairs made before it gets worse.  This has not created a 'safety hazard' yet but as time goes on the holes will get bigger and deeper potentially creating a hazard.

description: 10/8/20, street repair/blacktop crew came out to lay down blacktop.  I was advised Misty Harbor Avenue was to be surfaced.  The street in front of my property was only surfaced to the mailbox.  My property extends to 18 inches past the privacy fence.  The crew told me that my property is in the middle of 44th Street Terrace and Misty Harbor so they were going to stop it at the mailbox.  NO, my entire property is, and always HAS been on Misty Harbor Ave.  I am NOT on 44th Street Terrace.  The crew told me that my address was 'pinging' on 44th Street Terrace and they were not going to surface the road past my mailbox.  This is absolutely ridiculous.  In front of my driveway, half is surfaced, the other half, unsurfaced.  I was told that all of Misty Harbor Avenue would be surfaced, which includes the entire frontage of my home.  Furthermore, my property and the street itself is 17 years' old, and has never been resurfaced.  It has been patched so many times it looks like a relief map of South America.  HOWEVER, the newer streets to the North, that are less than five years of age and are largely unoccupied/new construction, were resurfaced!!  I would think after paying 17 years' worth of SPECIALS that I could get an additional 25-30 feet of resurfacing done.  It absolutely looks ridiculous.  There are two houses to the East of my property that are on 44th Street Terrace that would also have to be resurfaced, as those properties and streets are the same age and were entirely skipped, as well.  The homes in this area are in the 260k range and this takes away from the neighborhood; plus the uneven pavement is a definite safety issue.  I am very concerned that the city believes my property is half on Misty Harbor Ave., and half on 44th Street Terrace - because I guess if the city decides to resurface 44th Street Terrace, they won't surface Misty Harbor Avenue??  That's ridiculous, as well.  Please respond and please come back and finish this job, because it is ugly, and needs review.  Lastly, I did call the Engineering department yesterday and left a message for a Mr. Foust or Faust - of course, no call back.  Since there seems to be quite a bit of confusion of where I really live, I would suggest someone get into their city car and come out here and actually look at the ridiculousness of the situation, and view the street.
address: 4437 Sw Misty Harbor Ave Topeka, KS, 66610, USA

HOWEVER, the newer streets to the North, that are less than five years of age and are largely unoccupied/new construction, were resurfaced!!  I would think after paying 17 years' worth of SPECIALS that I could get an additional 25-30 feet of resurfacing done.  It absolutely looks ridiculous.  There are two houses to the East of my property that are on 44th Street Terrace that would also have to be resurfaced, as those properties and streets are the same age and were entirely skipped, as well.  The homes in this area are in the 260k range and this takes away from the neighborhood; plus the uneven pavement is a definite safety issue.  I am very concerned that the city believes my property is half on Misty Harbor Ave., and half on 44th Street Terrace - because I guess if the city decides to resurface 44th Street Terrace, they won't surface Misty Harbor Avenue??  That's ridiculous, as well.  Please respond and please come back and finish this job, because it is ugly, and needs review.  Lastly, I did call the Engineering department yesterday and left a message for a Mr. Foust or Faust - of course, no call back.  Since there seems to be quite a bit of confusion of where I really live, I would suggest someone get into their city car and come out here and actually look at the ridiculousness of the situation, and view the street.
address: 4437 Sw Misty Harbor Ave Topeka, KS, 66610, USA

We moved back out and hired a firm to rip out the carpet and trim boards, and dry everything out last summer. Then we built a French drain and a berm, to divert the water around our property.  So far that had been working, but this morning the rain came too fast, and the river channel forced the storm water back through our downspout toward the house, so we had to re-route the gutter and bail for hours to keep the house from flooding again.  We will try to fix it, but there is only a 5 foot strip beside our house to work with, so we're pretty limited.  In addition, one of the workers we've hired thinks our water bill will be raised because we are diverting so much storm water into the front sewer, even though the water is not coming from our lot. Any motor vehicle which shall have been found to have remained parked, stored or located upon any of the public streets or parkings of the city for a continuous period of more than 48 hours shall be deemed a public nuisance and such nuisance may be abated in the manner provided in this article. (Code 1981 § 43-388. Code 1995 § 142-353.)

description: Noticed your water tower at 29th & California is now getting long overdue repairs.  With the few upgrades I have seen from the ground there has been one thing that has bothered me for some time which the city keeps ignoring.  Your lighting issues.  Even though it may not be required for the height it is common courtesy in many cities that all municipal water storage tanks be properly lit with FAA approved lighting regardless if the tower is in line of airspace travel in that area of town. This tower for some time has not had a very well lit light if working at all especially recently since they did minor repairs late last year when they added the new tank access on the top of the storage tank.  I would hope you are going to invest in a new improved light, a LED/strobe version similar to what the VA hospital went with on the top of their tower a few years ago. No maintenance, no bulbs to change.  It's money well spent.  I also noticed you had someone raise your lighting on your Montara area water tower a while back to clear over all the obstacles that have been added to that one. Great job. Only issue is you have the same issue on your water tower behind the Soldier Township Fire Department. That light fixture also needs raised and or upgraded. With LED fixtures taking place of the older incandescent bulbs you should probably budget to upgrade all the lighting on your towers over time. As far as the one behind Soldier Township Fire Department you can't see that light working well at night because it's being blocked by all the clutter that's been added.  If Forbes Field and the V.A. takes lighting that seriously so should the city.  I hope you will seriously look into these issues....

This issue was reported almost 4 months ago and NOTHING has been done.  Homeowners’ pick-up truck with attached trailer is parked on street overnight every night and throughout many daytime hours.  Violates municipal code and worse, impairs traffic, including emergency traffic.

PLEASE address these issues with the homeowner.  Besides being in violation, homeowner degrades and devalues our whole area.

For reference:
10.70.010 Parking prohibited.
It shall be unlawful for any person to park or cause to be parked any truck tractor, trailer or semitrailer owned or under the physical control of such person, on any highway or street in the City, for a period of time longer than one hour of any day; provided, that this section shall not apply to vehicles owned by the United States of America, the State and the City or if otherwise allowed by City code.
As used herein, the term “park” or “cause to be parked” means the standing of a vehicle, whether occupied or not, otherwise than temporarily for the purpose of and while actually engaged in loading or unloading property or passengers or while engaged in residential or commercial construction or repair work. description: Hi, I am wondering who I need to contact to try to get the Topeka dog park to become smoke-free. I have gone there often for the last 6 years and my dog is very reactive to smoke. We usually go to the Lawrence dog park now which is tobacco-free because whenever we are in the Topeka dog park it seems like people are just not mindful of their cigarette smoke their cigarette butts and there is constantly the ashtray being knocked over. Today we were only there for a couple minutes before somebody inhales their cigarettes and looks down at my dog and blow the smoke directly in her face, I am just wondering if there is anything that can be done about this issue. The dog park is not really a place to be smoking cigars as is often done in the evenings but I feel that the dog park would be a much safer place for pets if the owners had a designated spot outside to go to versus just smoking everywhere in the park and properly disposing of their cigarette buds not just tossing them where are animals play. I know many dog parks have been going smoke-free and I was wondering if Topeka is going to follow that trend

description: Over time with rain this ditch running from the top of hill to the East down to Douglas Rd has filled with nearby field dirt and runoff. I have added small rock over time but that gets washed away with rain as well. I believe the whole ditch on the south side from the hill to Douglas St. needs to be dug out to allow water to drain from the ditch and not run down the side of the road. description:
There is a lot of dumping, and drag racing that is happening in the defunct development area SW of 46th and Lincolnshire.  Lots of nice city streets that people are using as a person drag strip, camping, drinking, etc.  My wife and I have hauled 2 pickup loads of trash from the are and there is just more every day.  Lots of people walk and ride bikes in the area due to little traffic, but it is becoming increasingly dangers with the cars and motorcycles racing around.  All one needs to do is look at all of the hundreds of burnout marks....I have pics, but it will only let me upload one.  I know the police can't be everywhere, and they have better things to do than to protect some vacant lots, but I had a suggestion I took to our HOA, and they suggested I contacted the city.  Why not put up some concrete barricades to block traffic on the 3 access roads to those hills, so only bike and foot traffic are allowed?  If someone needs to see the property, they can just drive around the blockade, but it will stop a good number of the folks racing and dumping all kinds of crazy stuff in the area.  If someone builds up there, then the barricades can be removed, but there is no need for the traffic in what is laughingly known by the local kids as the "420 Hills".

Joe Sellens
Laurens Way
630 464 8025

description: We bought this house in May 2019, and it began flooding shortly after we moved in. The owner said it had flooded once, and been repaired, but obviously lied.  It is the oldest house in the neighborhood; at least 3 of the surrounding houses, which were built up higher, have storm water drains flowing toward our back yard.  We moved back out and hired a firm to rip out the carpet and trim boards, and dry everything out last summer. Then we built a French drain and a berm, to divert the water around our property.  So far that had been working, but this morning the rain came too fast, and the river channel forced the storm water back through our downspout toward the house, so we had to re-route the gutter and bail for hours to keep the house from flooding again.  We will try to fix it, but there is only a 5 foot strip beside our house to work with, so we're pretty limited.  In addition, one of the workers we've hired thinks our water bill will be raised because we are diverting so much storm water into the front sewer, even though the water is not coming from our lot.  Could someone please come to look at this in person?

The center of Topeka needs work. 17th at Wannamaker, both east and west bound is STILL BUMPY! The holes they fixed are not even! how long does it take to scrape it and lay new asphalt? description: Residents let a very large brindle color dog out front door as we were walking on sidewalk with our dog, who was in a leash, then slammed their front door shut. The dog was charging, barking and snarling.  Startled, we backed up into the street into the path of a car who honked while we were trying to get away. Only then did we see where the dog had stopped at the sidewalk because it was tethered to a cable. We feel this is a dangerous situation as we have elderly people out walking, children walking and on bikes and many dog walkers in this neighborhood. Elderly people could fall and be injured, children could dart into oncoming traffic and dog fights/injuries could break out as pedestrian traffic tries to get away.  You do not know that the dog is on a cable and you are trying to get away from its intimidating charge, barking and snarling. We would like the residents/dog checked for city tags, current shots and perhaps the owners spoken to about placing their dog in the back yard in their fenced back yard.  A tethered cable is not safe enough.  We feel it’s a dangerous situation waiting to happen and needs a professional intervention.

10.60.100 Parking more than 48 hours.
It shall be unlawful for any person to park or permit the parking, storing or standing of any vehicle upon any public street or street parking in the city for any continuous period of more than 48 hours. Any motor vehicle which shall have been found to have remained parked, stored or located upon any of the public streets or parkings of the city for a continuous period of more than 48 hours shall be deemed a public nuisance and such nuisance may be abated in the manner provided in this article. When we returned, my wife had a flat tire, actually the tire was cut and not repairable.  On our ride we noticed the bike lanes had a lot of debris in them, glass, rocks, tree limbs, etc. This debris was obviously the cause of the flat tire.  If you want cyclists to use the bike lanes it is going to be imperative the city keep them clean.  Another issue is bike lanes and parking being used in the same space. description:
Silver Ford Escape parked on the street vehicle hasn't moved for several months.  A request was submitted recently and then closed.  I wasn't able to comment on the closed request so I am opening a new one in order to communicate my concerns.

I am at a loss to your response.  As a citizen I expect the laws of our city to be enforced when they are pointed out to our police department.  This car may not seem like it is bothering anything to the officer who only stops by for a brief minute but is does affect the quality of life for the neighbors in the area.  The car has not moved for over 6 months and there are even weeds starting to grow around the car.  Our city code clearly state a car cannot sit in one place for more than 48 hours.  This car has sat in the same location for an access of 4300 hours.  I am sure this vehicle fits the intent of the code.  I am not asking for a ticket I am asking that the police department take action and see that this car is moved and in compliance with our city code.  I have attached the code in case you are not aware of what you are expected to enforce.   In addition if that car is not registered to anyone at that house or someone nearby then I would think it would be considered abandoned having more of a reason to remove it.
10.60.100 Parking more than 48 hours.
It shall be unlawful for any person to park or permit the parking, storing or standing of any vehicle upon any public street or street parking in the city for any continuous period of more than 48 hours. Any motor vehicle which shall have been found to have remained parked, stored or located upon any of the public streets or parkings of the city for a continuous period of more than 48 hours shall be deemed a public nuisance and such nuisance may be abated in the manner provided in this article.
address: 5900-5916 Sw 28th Ter Topeka, KS, 66614, USA

description: Noticed your water tower at 29th & California is now getting long overdue repairs.  With the few upgrades I have seen from the ground there has been one thing that has bothered me for some time which the city keeps ignoring.  Your lighting issues.  Even though it may not be required for the height it is common courtesy in many cities that all municipal water storage tanks be properly lit with FAA approved lighting regardless if the tower is in line of airspace travel in that area of town. This tower for some time has not had a very well lit light if working at all especially recently since they did minor repairs late last year when they added the new tank access on the top of the storage tank.  I would hope you are going to invest in a new improved light, a LED/strobe version similar to what the VA hospital went with on the top of their tower a few years ago. No maintenance, no bulbs to change.  It's money well spent.  I also noticed you had someone raise your lighting on your Montara area water tower a while back to clear over all the obstacles that have been added to that one. Great job. Only issue is you have the same issue on your water tower behind the Soldier Township Fire Department. That light fixture also needs raised and or upgraded. With LED fixtures taking place of the older incandescent bulbs you should probably budget to upgrade all the lighting on your towers over time. As far as the one behind Soldier Township Fire Department you can't see that light working well at night because it's being blocked by all the clutter that's been added.  If Forbes Field and the V.A. takes lighting that seriously so should the city.  I hope you will seriously look into these issues....
address: 1930 Se 29th St Topeka, KS, 66605, USA
